250 g Ground Beef
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
½ cup Tomato Salsa
8 g Enchilada Spice Blend
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
½ unit(s) Carrot
2 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
2 unit(s) Green Onion
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Peel, then grate half the carrot (use whole carrot for 4 servings).
Thinly slice green onions.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then carrot and beef. Cook for 4-5 min, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with salt and pepper.
Carefully drain and discard excess fat.

To the pan with beef, add Enchilada Spice Blend, garlic puree, tomato sauce base, 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water and half the green onions.
Cook for 2-3 min, stirring often, until fragrant and sauce thickens slightly. Season with salt and pepper.

Wrap tortillas in paper towels. Microwave for 1 min, until tortillas are warm and flexible. (TIP: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm the tortillas!)

Divide tortillas between plates, then top with beef filling.
Top tacos, as you like, with cheese, mild salsa, sour cream and remaining green onions.